{\line }

{\line }
As she turned around to start walking back towards her house, she froze where she lay when a mailed hand seemed to stretch from a shadowy crevice, some chasm in a wall she hadn\uc1\u8217't noticed in her dimly lit surroundings: it was a surreptitious figure that seemed well-disposed towards her, or else she would be already lying in a pool of her own blood for what little coin she carried in her tiny purse. She shuddered at the thought that worse things than an untimely death could have happened to her that she dared not imagine while carrying her child still in her womb. The figure spoke to her in a curt, hushed voice:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"Lady Celia, be still and fear not. I am Kin, and I bear news for you: Philo has been arrested, but your husband is nowhere to be found.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
Her voice quavered in shock and vibrated with disbelief:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"And Amonas?What of him?Is he dead?\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
