{\line }
Lanris was hugging his face with one hand, always surprised at the ways Mott could sound like a complete dolt. Pirru went on:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"Something like that. Anyway, yes, I went to the \uc1\u8217'Cent. \uc1\u8217'One hundred per cent guaranteed\uc1\u8217' Tibodot, the little rat. But I got my coin\uc1\u8217's worth now. He wasn\uc1\u8217't selling cow dung this time. I asked the Centarch somewhat sideways if all was going as planned, and he too said there was some upheaval upstairs. Some stuff would be put on hold until further notice. That\uc1\u8217's probably the reason I\uc1\u8217'm not putting the pair of you on auxiliary tomorrow. The auxiliary\uc1\u8217's been abandoned. All men are rotating back in their usual duties, as per regulation. Lanris, you are lucky bastards.\uc1\u8221"
