{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"Well, going into the Widelands seemed strange. But orders are orders, right? So now, when we get new orders, they\uc1\u8217'll still be orders. I don\uc1\u8217't think it changes anything. About me at least. As long as I get my uwe and even if I have to put up with Mott\uc1\u8217's cooking, it doesn\uc1\u8217't mean much. Just one thousand four hundred and thirty one days to go, dekar. That\uc1\u8217's all that counts for me.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"You\uc1\u8217're all the same, you conscripts. You just want to get on with your lives, like it gets any better out there. Still, I don\uc1\u8217't blame you. If something\uc1\u8217's going to kill you, it doesn\uc1\u8217't really matter where that will happen. I just happen to find change a bad thing, that\uc1\u8217's all.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"You\uc1\u8217're not trying to drag me down in one of your morose spells, are you?\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
Pirru nodded while shrugging, an almost disarming and childlike reaction from a dekar well-nigh six feet tall. After a short silence was observed, he grinned to Lanris before replying:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"I got wine. Not winegar, but real wine.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
Lanris forehead creased in a conspirator\uc1\u8217's furrow:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"How did you get by that, I wonder?\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
The dekar replied in a hushed voice, a measure of pride in his words:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"Smuggled some from the centarch\uc1\u8217's cabinet. This stuff is guaranteed.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
Lanris scratched his chin thoughtfully while he seemed to contemplate the risks involved, and said:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"I see. So, we\uc1\u8217're both risking forty lashes.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
Dekar Pirru waved a hand dismissively and replied:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"Twenty for me, I\uc1\u8217'll pull rank.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
They both laughed, somewhat bitterly despite themselves. Pirru checked hastily around, not really bothering to indeed look for procrastinators or senior officers lurking in the dark, but rather as an instinctive reaction to fear of getting caught. He reached into his uniform and produced a small leather flask, no bigger than their issued water flask. He unsealed it and gave it to Lanris. He said with a wide grin of accomplishment:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"Smell that? Pure Decau wine.\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
Lanris took a whiff, grimaced and shuddered reflexively. He gave the flask back to Pirru with exasperation in his voice:
{\line }

{\line }
