{\line }

{\line }
As these announcements had been made in front of the whole army, the few procrastinators spread around the staging grounds having received word of the General\uc1\u8217's orders fled with alacrity in an unusual sign of intelligence.
{\line }

{\line }
And so it had begun, the campaign that would forever change the history of the Outer Territories for better, or for worse.
{\line }

{\line }
The General had been musing on these recent past events for some time it seemed, because he could hear anxiety and worry in the words that his adjutant repeated in the same staccato manner:
{\line }

{\line }
\uc1\u8220"Sir, are you alright? Sir? Should I call for your physician, sir? Sir? Are you alright?\uc1\u8221"
{\line }

{\line }
